TITLE: Updating Interest Groups in C# using Photon Realtime API
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to update Interest Groups for a client in the Particle Demo. It checks the current group and calls OpChangeGroups to update the server with the client's interests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/xsampedro/quantum3_docs/blob/main/output/realtime/getting-started/quick-start.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
private void UpdateInterestGroups()
{
    if (this.UseInterestGroups)
    {
        byte currentGroup = this.GetGroup(this.LocalPlayer);
        if (currentGroup != this.LocalPlayer.VisibleGroup)
        {
            this.RealtimeClient.OpChangeGroups(new byte[0], new byte[] { currentGroup });     // config the server to only send this group
            this.LocalPlayer.VisibleGroup = currentGroup;                               // store which group we now are interested in (server side)
        }
    }
}
```

